   Treaties Synopsis Minutes Joint Reports

   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   The Foreign Affairs Office reports to the Office of the United States
   Commissioner. This office supports the United States Commissioner in
   his charge of joining with the Mexican Commissioner in application  of
   the obligations and rights assumed by the United States and Mexican
   Governments in the several boundary and water treaties and IBWC
   agreements.  The Foreign Affairs Office is headed by the United States
   Section Secretary who with the Mexican Section Secretary control the
   diplomatic communications of the IBWC and, accompany the Commissioners
   to IBWC meetings. They prepare the IBWC formal agreements, IBWC
   Minutes, in English and Spanish and keep records of all  discussions
   and understandings reached at those meetings, as well as advise on
   protocol. They serve as Spanish and English language interpreters. The
   U.S. Section Secretary also serves as a policy adviser on domestic
   relations and, in liaison with the Department of State, serves as an
   expert adviser on boundary and water treaty and IBWC agreement
   interpretations.

